<task id="035" project="ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>D6 â€” spaarke-insights-index scope shape generalization (carry entityType + entityId)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <wave>D</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2d</estimated-effort>
    <tags>azure-ai-search, index-schema, migration, multi-entity, infra</tags>
    <dependencies>015</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <wave-item>D6</wave-item>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Evolve the spaarke-insights-index schema to carry scope.entityType + scope.entityId alongside the existing scope.matterId (hybrid backward-compat per A6 + spec.md Q-D6-1 option c). Migrate Phase 1 Observations so they remain queryable. New Observations written by universal-ingest@v1 carry the new fields.
  </prompt>

  <role>Azure AI Search engineer + index migration specialist.</role>

  <goal>
    spaarke-insights-index schema includes scope.entityType + scope.entityId (both filterable + searchable). Phase 1 Observations migrated (entityType defaulted to "matter", entityId populated from existing matterId). New Observations from universal-ingest carry both old (matterId for backward compat) and new (entityType + entityId) fields. Index-write path in BFF updated. Index-read path in BFF supports filtering by either field.
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="a6-design">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-a6-multi-entity.md (migration plan)</file>
    <file purpose="r1-index-schema">infra/insights/schemas/spaarke-insights-index.json (current schema)</file>
    <file purpose="r1-bicep">infra/insights/modules/ (index infra)</file>
    <file purpose="knowledge">knowledge/azure-ai-search/ (AI Search migration patterns)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec.md NFR-08">Phase 1 Observations must remain queryable after migration</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Index changes flow through Zone A (Services/Ai/) infra</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Verify Bicep + publish-size impact</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Decide migration mechanism">In-place add nullable fields (cheaper) vs re-create index + reindex (cleaner). Initial leaning: in-place if Azure AI Search supports add-field; otherwise re-create.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Update schema JSON">Add scope.entityType (filterable string) + scope.entityId (filterable string)</step>
    <step order="3" name="Bicep update">Apply schema change via existing infra/insights/modules/</step>
    <step order="4" name="Migrate Phase 1 Observations">Backfill entityType="matter" + entityId=matterId for existing Observations (may require batch update via Azure CLI / SDK)</step>
    <step order="5" name="Update BFF index-write path">Universal-ingest emits both old (matterId) + new (entityType + entityId) fields</step>
    <step order="6" name="Update BFF index-read path">Support filtering by either field; default new queries to entityType + entityId</step>
    <step order="7" name="Smoke verify">(a) Phase 1 Observation still queryable by matterId; (b) New Observation queryable by entityType + entityId</step>
    <step order="8" name="Quality gates">code-review + adr-check; coordinate with infra team for prod migration plan</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="config">infra/insights/schemas/spaarke-insights-index.json (modified)</output>
    <output type="bicep">infra/insights/modules/ (modified)</output>
    <output type="code">BFF index-write + index-read paths updated</output>
    <output type="migration-script">scripts/Migrate-InsightsIndexScopeShape.ps1 (or similar)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">spaarke-insights-index carries scope.entityType + scope.entityId</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Phase 1 Observations migrated and queryable by matterId (backward compat)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">New Observations queryable by entityType + entityId</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Bicep apply clean on Spaarke Dev</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">spec.md NFR-08 + FR-03 satisfied</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    <completion-date>2026-06-03</completion-date>
    <completed-by>task-execute (parallel Wave D-G4 dispatch alongside 032, 034)</completed-by>

    <decisions>
      <decision id="D6-D1">In-place schema additions (NOT v2 + back-fill) â€” no live Phase 1 data in spaarke-insights-index yet, Azure AI Search supports adding new filterable string fields in place, Bicep PUT is idempotent. Design-a6 Â§5.1's "re-create required" assumption was overcautious for the field types we're adding.</decision>
      <decision id="D6-D2">Top-level `scope` ComplexType (matches design-a6 Â§4.5 OData filter notation `scope/matterId eq 'â€¦'`). Existing `value/raw/scope/{matterType,opposingCounsel}` preserved for backward compat (zero current consumers).</decision>
      <decision id="D6-D3">Feature flag named `Insights:Index:DualWriteScopeMatterId` (bool, default true on `AiSearchOptions`). Toggles writer emission of legacy `scope.matterId` for matter subjects. Reader OR-filter logic is unaffected by this flag â€” flipping it doesn't break reads.</decision>
      <decision id="D6-D4">Reader filter generated at runtime from a new optional `subjectScope` config field on `IndexRetrieveNode`. Matter subjects emit hybrid OR-filter `(scope/matterId eq â€¦ or (scope/entityType eq 'matter' and scope/entityId eq â€¦))`; non-matter schemes emit canonical narrow-filter `(scope/entityType eq â€¦ and scope/entityId eq â€¦)`.</decision>
      <decision id="D6-D5">Back-fill script (`scripts/Migrate-InsightsIndexScopeShape.ps1`) defensively created even though Phase 1 has no live observations. Idempotent merge-upserts; NFR-08 verification step samples 5 matter-subject Observations post-migration. Owner can dry-run + apply.</decision>
      <decision id="D6-D6">Parallel-task collision (with 034): InsightsModule.cs line 83 updated to reference `MatterLiveFactResolver` (the class 034 created when renaming `DataverseLiveFactResolver`). This is a STOPGAP â€” task 034's dictionary-keyed registration per design-a6 Â§3.4 will subsume this line.</decision>
    </decisions>

