    <deploy-ordering>
      <step order="1">Apply Bicep: `az deployment group create -f infra/insights/main.bicep -p infra/insights/parameters/dev.json -g spe-infrastructure-westus2` â€” adds `scope` ComplexType to spaarke-insights-index (idempotent PUT).</step>
      <step order="2">Verify schema change in portal or via REST: `GET https://spaarke-search-dev.search.windows.net/indexes/spaarke-insights-index?api-version=2024-07-01` should show top-level `scope` field.</step>
      <step order="3">[Skipped for spaarke-search-dev â€” no Phase 1 data] Run back-fill script: `.\scripts\Migrate-InsightsIndexScopeShape.ps1 -SearchServiceName spaarke-search-dev -KeyVaultName sprkspaarkedev-aif-kv -AdminKeySecretName SearchAdminKey -DryRun` (then drop `-DryRun` to apply).</step>
      <step order="4">Deploy BFF (`/bff-deploy`) â€” writer will start dual-writing scope fields immediately; reader supports `subjectScope` config in `IndexRetrieveNode`. Default dual-write flag is ON.</step>
      <step order="5">Soak in production with reader OR-filter active. Phase 1 backward-compat is preserved by reader logic + writer dual-write.</step>
      <step order="6">After â‰Ą1 sprint soak with no rollback events, optionally set `Insights:Index:DualWriteScopeMatterId=false` to stop emitting legacy `scope.matterId` for matter subjects (reader OR-filter continues working, so historical Observations remain queryable).</step>
    </deploy-ordering>

    <rollback-plan>
      <mechanism>Single config-toggle revert: set `Insights:Index:DualWriteScopeMatterId=false` in App Settings â†’ writer stops emitting `scope.matterId` for matter subjects. Reader OR-filter is unaffected (Phase 1 historical observations stay queryable). Schema addition is non-destructive (additive nullable fields); no schema rollback needed.</mechanism>
      <mechanism>Hard rollback: redeploy previous BFF revision (writer + reader revert in lockstep). Schema additions in the index remain (no impact â€” fields stay null).</mechanism>
    </rollback-plan>

